PC Number Date Chapter Bill Dept
 2021-10532021-12-20,  ,  FA,  , 
ActOther Than Statutory Authority
PrecisAppointment of RAJANI ALEXANDER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Guatemala, with concurrent accreditation as High Commissioner for Canada in Belize, with residence in Guatemala City; NADIA BURGER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Indonesia; MICHAEL CALLAN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the People’s Democratic Republic of Algeria;LILIAN CHATTERJEE as High Commissioner for Canada in Grenada and as non-resident Consul General of Canada in the British Virgin Islands, with residence in Bridgetown; CHRISTOPHER COOTER as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Mauritius, as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Namibia and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Madagascar, with residence in Pretoria; KATHLEEN CSABA as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Sierra Leone, with residence in Accra; CLAUDE DEMERS as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Liberia, with residence in Abidjan; MARK FLETCHER as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Korea;GREGORY GALLIGAN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Iraq;ELISSA GOLBERG as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Malta and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Albania, with residence in Rome;ALAN HAMSON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Kazakhstan, with concurrent accreditations as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Kyrgyz Republic and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Tajikistan, with residence in Nur-Sultan;PATRICK HÉBERT as Consul General of Canada in Chandigarh (Republic of India);LEE-ANNE HERMANN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Burkina Faso and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Benin, with residence in Ouagadougou;DIEDRAH KELLY as Consul General of Canada in Mumbai (Republic of India); JOANNE LEMAY as High Commissioner for Canada in the Kingdom of Tonga, as High Commissioner for Canada in the Independent State of Samoa and as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Kiribati, with residence in Wellington;TROY LULASHNYK as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Austria and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Slovak Republic, with residence in Vienna; CAMERON MACKAY as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of India, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Federal Democratic Republic of Nepal, with residence in New Delhi;LILLY NICHOLLS as High Commissioner for Canada in the People’s Republic of Bangladesh;BENOIT PRÉFONTAINE as Consul General of Canada in Bangalore (Republic of India);WAYNE ROBSON as High Commissioner for Canada in Malaysia;REID SIRRS as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Argentine Republic, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Paraguay, with residence in Buenos Aires;CHRISTOPHER THORNLEY as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Kenya and Permanent Representative of Canada to the United Nations Human Settlements Program and to the United Nations Environment Program; ELIZABETH WILLIAMS as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Nicaragua, with residence in San José; and PATRICK WITTMANN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Swiss Confederation, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Principality of Liechtenstein, with residence in Bern.
